galit lipa stanford law school stanford law school search utility navigation test directory news center library events publications contact & maps information for prospective students alumni employers current students faculty & staff directory galit lipa lecturer go back biography galit lipa joined stanford law school in 2007 as a fellow in the criminal defense clinic lipa was most recently a deputy public defender at the contra costa county office of the public defender prior to that she was an e barrett prettyman fellow at georgetown university law center where she represented people accused of crimes in misdemeanor felonies and delinquency hearings in washington dc s superior court and supervised third year students in the juvenile justice clinic who were representing clients in delinquency proceedings she is a 2004 graduate of yale law school and in 2006 was awarded an llm from georgetown law in advocacy field of interest expertise criminal law and criminal justice criminal procedure juvenile justice glipa law stanford edu 650 723.1422 cloudy 56 f 2012 stanford university system requirements help virtual tour
